# Week 15 - Day 5: Course Schedule II (LeetCode 210)

## 📌 Problem Statement
There are `numCourses` courses labeled from `0` to `n-1`.

You are given prerequisites:

👉 Return **any valid order** of courses you can take  
👉 If impossible (cycle exists), return **empty array**

---

## 🚀 Approach (BFS - Kahn’s Algorithm)

This is an extension of **LeetCode 207**.

Instead of just checking feasibility:
👉 We **return the topological order**

---

## 🧠 Key Idea

1. Build graph (adjacency list)  
2. Compute indegree of each node  
3. Push all nodes with indegree = 0 into queue  
4. Perform BFS:
   - Remove node
   - Add it to answer
   - Reduce indegree of neighbors  
   - Push new indegree 0 nodes  

---

## 🔥 Logic

- If result size == total nodes → valid order ✅  
- Else → cycle exists → return empty ❌  

---

## ⚡ Time Complexity
- **O(V + E)**

## 💾 Space Complexity
- **O(V + E)**

---
  class Solution {
public:
    bool iscycleDFS(int src, vector<bool>& vis, vector<bool>& recpath,
                    vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        vis[src] = true;
        recpath[src] = true;

        // finding it's neighbours
        for (int i = 0; i < edges.size(); i++) {
            int v = edges[i][0];
            int u = edges[i][1];

            if (src == u) {
                if (!vis[v]) {
                    if (iscycleDFS(v, vis, recpath, edges)) {
                        return true;
                    }
                } else if (recpath[v]) {
                    return true;
                }
            }
        }

        recpath[src] = false;
        return false;
    }

    // topo sort
    void topoOrder(int src, stack<int>& s, vector<bool>& vis,
                   vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        vis[src] = true;

        for (int i = 0; i < edges.size(); i++) {
            int v = edges[i][0];
            int u = edges[i][1];

            if (src == u) {
                if (!vis[v]) {
                    topoOrder(v, s, vis, edges);
                }
            }
        }
        s.push(src);
    }

    vector<int> findOrder(int n, vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        vector<bool> vis(n, false);
        vector<bool> recpath(n, false);
        vector<int> ans;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (!vis[i]) {
                if (iscycleDFS(i, vis, recpath, edges)) {
                    return ans;
                }
            }
        }

        // topological sorted order
        stack<int> s;
        vis.assign(n, false);
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (!vis[i]) {
                 topoOrder(i, s, vis, edges);
            }
        }
        // extracting answer from stack
        while (s.size() > 0) {
            ans.push_back(s.top());
            s.pop();
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

